{"title_page": "Przec\u0142aw of Pogorzela", "text_new": "'''Przec\u0142aw of Pogorzela''' (Polish: Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli) (ca. 1310 &ndash; 6 April 1376 in Otmuch\u00f3w) was a [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]] and [[Bishop of Wroc\u0142aw]] from 1342\u20131376. <ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/wroc0.htm  Bishops of Wroclaw] at GCatholic.org.</ref>\n\nPrzec\u0142aw of Pogorzela was born around 1310 into noble family in the Duchy of Brze\u015bc.<ref name=sil>[https://silesia.edu.pl/index.php?title=Przec%C5%82aw_z_Pogorzeli Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli]</ref>. By April 1329 was [[canon (priest)|Canon]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wroc\u0142aw#Within Bohemia|Wroc\u0142aw]]. In 1336 he visited [[Bologna]] to study. \n\nOn 5 May 1341 he was elected [[Bishop]] of [[Wroc\u0142aw]], however due to opposition of the [[primate of Poland|Archbishop of Gniezno]], [[Janis\u0142aw I|Janis\u0142aw]], he had to personally go to [[Avignon#Avignon and its popes|Avignon]] for [[pope|Papal]] approval, which was confirmed on 28 January 1342.\n\nA tireless builder, he oversaw the completion of [[Wroclaw Cathedral]], built the Church of [[Stanislaus of Szczepan\u00f3w|St. Stanislaus]], and Dorothy, the chapel of St. Mary's [[Church building|Church]] and Joseph's [[Hospital]] in [[Nysa, Poland|Nysa]]. He also founded [[Carmelite]], [[Carthusian]], [[Augustinians|Augustinian]] and [[Benedictine]] [[monasteries]].  He introduced the feast of St. [[Jadwiga]] and also had audiences with [[Holy Roman Emperor|Emperor]] [[Charles IV of Luxembourg]] and [[Casimir the Great]]. In 1348, he purchased the castle of [[J\u00e1nsk\u00fd vrch]] from [[Bolko II the Small|Bolko II]] of [[\u015awidnica]], and turned it into the palace of the prince-bishops of Wroc\u0142aw.\n\nHe died on the night of 5 to 6 April 1376 in Otmuch\u00f3w.<ref name=sil/> and was buried in the chapel of St. Mary's Church, [[Wroc\u0142aw Cathedral]], in a marble sarcophagus. His has been considered a \"golden age\" of the bishopric of Wroc\u0142aw.\n\n== Footnotes ==\n<references />\n\n== References ==\n*[https://silesia.edu.pl/index.php?title=Przec%C5%82aw_z_Pogorzeli Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli]\n{{s-start}}\n\n{{s-rel}}\n{{succession box |\nbefore= [[Henryk z Wierzbnej]] |\ntitle=[[Bishop of Wroc\u0142aw]] |\nyears= 1342\u20131376   |\nafter= [[Wenceslaus II of Legnica]] }}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Prince-Bishops of Breslau]]\n[[Category:14th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:1310 births]]\n[[Category:1376 deaths]]\n\n\n{{cardinal-stub}}\n{{Poland-RC-bishop-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Przec\u0142aw of Pogorzela''' (Polish: Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli) (ca. 1310 &ndash; 6 April 1376 in Otmuch\u00f3w) was a [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]] and [[Bishop of Wroc\u0142aw]] from 1342\u20131376. <ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/wroc0.htm  Bishops of Wroclaw] at GCatholic.org.</ref>\n\nPrzec\u0142aw of Pogorzela was born around 1310 into noble family in the Duchy of Brze\u015bc.<ref name=sil>[https://silesia.edu.pl/index.php?title=Przec%C5%82aw_z_Pogorzeli Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli]</ref>. By April 1329 was [[canon (priest)|Canon]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wroc\u0142aw#Within Bohemia|Wroc\u0142aw]]. In 1336 he visited [[Bologna]] to study. \n\nOn 5 May 1341 he was elected [[Bishop]] of [[Wroc\u0142aw]], however due to opposition of the [[primate of Poland|Archbishop of Gniezno]], [[Janis\u0142aw I|Janis\u0142aw]], he had to personally go to [[Avignon#Avignon and its popes|Avignon]] for [[pope|Papal]] approval, which was confirmed on 28 January 1342.\n\nA tireless builder, he oversaw the completion of [[Wroclaw Cathedral]], built the Church of [[Stanislaus of Szczepan\u00f3w|St. Stanislaus]], and Dorothy, the chapel of St. Mary's [[Church building|Church]] and Joseph's [[Hospital]] in [[Nysa, Poland|Nysa]]. He also founded [[Carmelite]], [[Carthusian]], [[Augustinian]] and [[Benedictine]] [[monasteries]].  He introduced the feast of St. [[Jadwiga]] and also had audiences with [[Holy Roman Emperor|Emperor]] [[Charles IV of Luxembourg]] and [[Casimir the Great]]. In 1348, he purchased the castle of [[J\u00e1nsk\u00fd vrch]] from [[Bolko II the Small|Bolko II]] of [[\u015awidnica]], and turned it into the palace of the prince-bishops of Wroc\u0142aw.\n\nHe died on the night of 5 to 6 April 1376 in Otmuch\u00f3w.<ref name=sil/> and was buried in the chapel of St. Mary's Church, [[Wroc\u0142aw Cathedral]], in a marble sarcophagus. His has been considered a \"golden age\" of the bishopric of Wroc\u0142aw.\n\n== Footnotes ==\n<references />\n\n== References ==\n*[https://silesia.edu.pl/index.php?title=Przec%C5%82aw_z_Pogorzeli Przec\u0142aw z Pogorzeli]\n{{s-start}}\n\n{{s-rel}}\n{{succession box |\nbefore= [[Henryk z Wierzbnej]] |\ntitle=[[Bishop of Wroc\u0142aw]] |\nyears= 1342\u20131376   |\nafter= [[Wenceslaus II of Legnica]] }}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Prince-Bishops of Breslau]]\n[[Category:14th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:1310 births]]\n[[Category:1376 deaths]]\n\n\n{{cardinal-stub}}\n{{Poland-RC-bishop-stub}}\n", "name_user": "BD2412", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Fixinglinks to disambiguation pages, replaced:Augustinian\u2192Augustinian", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Przec%C5%82aw_of_Pogorzela"}
